cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper involves the development of a framework for training locomotor skills and visually guided manipulation of objects, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO). The approach involves the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with the challenges of task specification, exploration, and generalization, which are relevant to the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY).
